Universal CI/CD Pack — Environment Variables Template
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
VERSION: 1.0.0
CREATED: 2026-02-16
PURPOSE: Master configuration for repo-agnostic CI/CD workflows
SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Copy this file and fill in your values
2. Run: bash .github/scripts/setup-repo-vars.sh [your-env-file]
OR set manually in: GitHub → Settings → Secrets and Variables → Variables
ZERO-CONFIG DEFAULT: All workflows work immediately with sensible defaults.
Configure only what you need to customize.
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 1: Project Identity
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Project name (used in Kubernetes namespaces, Helm releases, labels)
Default: repository name (auto-detected)
PROJECT_NAME=

Primary branch name (main development branch)
Default: main
PRIMARY_BRANCH=main

Development branch name (if using GitFlow)
Default: develop
DEVELOP_BRANCH=develop

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 2: Python Configuration
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Python version for CI/CD
Default: 3.12
PYTHON_VERSION=3.12

Python requirements file path
Default: requirements.txt
REQUIREMENTS_FILE=requirements.txt

Minimum test coverage percentage (fails build if below threshold)
Default: 60
COVERAGE_THRESHOLD=60

Test directory path (relative to repo root)
Default: tests/
TEST_DIR=tests/

Source code directory (for coverage reports)
Default: . (entire repo)
SOURCE_DIR=.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 3: Container Registry Configuration
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Container registry host
Default: ghcr.io (GitHub Container Registry)
REGISTRY=ghcr.io

Container image name (omit to auto-detect from github.repository)
Default: (empty — uses owner/repo format)
Example: myorg/myapp
IMAGE_NAME=

Build target platforms (comma-separated)
Default: linux/amd64,linux/arm64
BUILD_PLATFORMS=linux/amd64,linux/arm64

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 4: Kubernetes / Helm Deployment
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Helm chart path (relative to repo root)
Default: deploy/helm/chart
HELM_CHART_PATH=deploy/helm/chart

Helm CLI version
Default: 3.16.3
HELM_VERSION=3.16.3

Helm release name prefix (environments append -prod / -staging)
Default: $PROJECT_NAME (auto-detected from repo name)
HELM_RELEASE_PREFIX=

Production Kubernetes namespace
Default: {project}-prod
PROD_NAMESPACE=

Staging Kubernetes namespace
Default: {project}-staging
STAGING_NAMESPACE=

Production application URL (for smoke tests and GitHub environment URL)
Default: https://{project}.example.com
PROD_URL=

Staging application URL
Default: https://staging.{project}.example.com
STAGING_URL=

Production replica count
Default: 3
PROD_REPLICAS=3

Staging replica count
Default: 1
STAGING_REPLICAS=1

Health check endpoint path
Default: /health
HEALTH_ENDPOINT=/health

Version/info endpoint path (for smoke tests)
Default: /api/v1/version
VERSION_ENDPOINT=/api/v1/version

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 5: Optional Feature Toggles
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Enable PostgreSQL test service in CI
Default: false
POSTGRES_ENABLED=false

PostgreSQL Docker image for tests
Default: postgres:16
POSTGRES_IMAGE=postgres:16

PostgreSQL test user
Default: test_user
POSTGRES_USER=test_user

PostgreSQL test database
Default: test_db
POSTGRES_DB=test_db

Enable Redis test service in CI
Default: false
REDIS_ENABLED=false

Redis Docker image for tests
Default: redis:7-alpine
REDIS_IMAGE=redis:7-alpine

Enable Neo4j test service in CI
Default: false
NEO4J_ENABLED=false

Neo4j Docker image for tests
Default: neo4j:5-community
NEO4J_IMAGE=neo4j:5-community

Enable Slack notifications for deployments
Default: false (set to 'true' and configure SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL secret)
SLACK_NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED=false

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 6: Pull Request Policies
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

PR size: lines changed warning threshold (adds comment)
Default: 300
PR_WARN_LINES=300

PR size: lines changed blocking threshold (fails check)
Default: 1000
PR_BLOCK_LINES=1000

PR size: maximum files changed
Default: 50
PR_MAX_FILES=50

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 7: Supply Chain Security / Licensing
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Allowed open-source licenses (comma-separated SPDX identifiers)
Default: MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD-3-Clause, BSD-2-Clause, ISC
ALLOWED_LICENSES=MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD-3-Clause, BSD-2-Clause, ISC

Denied open-source licenses (comma-separated SPDX identifiers)
Default: GPL-3.0, AGPL-3.0
DENIED_LICENSES=GPL-3.0, AGPL-3.0

pip-licenses allow-only string (semicolon-separated)
Default: MIT;Apache-2.0;BSD-3-Clause;BSD-2-Clause;ISC;Python Software Foundation License;Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL 2.0)
PIP_LICENSES_ALLOW=MIT;Apache-2.0;BSD-3-Clause;BSD-2-Clause;ISC;Python Software Foundation License;Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL 2.0)

pip-licenses fail-on string (semicolon-separated)
Default: GPL-3.0;AGPL-3.0;LGPL-3.0
PIP_LICENSES_DENY=GPL-3.0;AGPL-3.0;LGPL-3.0

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 8: Secrets (DO NOT STORE VALUES HERE — SET VIA GITHUB SECRETS)
These are references only — configure in GitHub Settings → Secrets
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GITHUB_TOKEN          — Auto-provided by GitHub Actions (no setup needed)
KUBECONFIG            — Kubernetes cluster config (base64-encoded) [required for k8s-deploy]
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL     — Slack incoming webhook URL [optional, for notifications]
CODECOV_TOKEN         — Codecov upload token [optional, for coverage reports]

